                    <h6>What is the plan for September 15?</h6>
                    <p>The World Cleanup Day Armenia team will publish 11 maps, one per region, on the official page of the movement
                        (www.cleanuparmenia.org).
                        Each map will be divided into zones, which will be coordinated by a local leader.
                    </p>
                    <p>Any participant will be able to cleanup his or her backyard or to open a map of his or her area, choose the most convenient zone, and go there. The action will begin at 10:00 am on Saturday and
                        will last for three hours. The local leader will tell the participants about the types of waste and recycling options in Armenia, will show the territory, and will help along the way. There will be photo and video shooting, and the participation of celebrities is planned.
                        The local leader will check that the waste is safely collected.</p>
                    <p>A large-scale advertising campaign of World Cleanup Day Armenia will begin on August 15. The final video about the initiative will be distributed through international media to show the results in Armenia to the whole world.</p>
